<p>I'm trying to send some simple <code>ZPL command</code> (for example : Hello World) to the <code>printer</code> through <code>serial port</code> but I'm not sure if I'm doing it right. The <code>COM port</code> from printer is already open and then I'm doing this part of the code below where the data will send to <code>serial port</code></p>  <pre><code>serialport.on('data', function (data) {  var str =     "^XA\r\n" +     "^FO50,50\r\n" +     "^A0N50,50\r\n" +     "^FDHello world^FS\r\n" +     "^XZ"; buffer = new Buffer(str.length);  for (var i = 0; i &lt; str.length; i++) {     buffer[i] = str.charCodeAt(i); }      data = buffer.toString();     this.serialport.write(data, function (error, result) {         if (error) {             console.log('[FAILURE] : ' + error);         }         if (result) {             console.log('result: ' + result);         }     }); }) </code></pre>